There she blows!

11
00:01:53,107 --> 00:01:56,352
Had the trump of judgment blown, they could not have quivered more.

12
00:01:56,793 --> 00:02:03,542
Yet still they felt no terror or rather pleasure, for though it was a most unwanted hour,

13
00:02:03,522 --> 00:02:12,194
Yet so impressive was the cry, and so deliriously exciting, that almost every soul on board instinctively desired a lowering.

14
00:02:12,274 --> 00:02:21,787
Walking the deck with quick side-lunging strides, Ahab commanded the tuggalant sails and royals to be set, and every stunned sail spread.

15
00:02:21,807 --> 00:02:25,092
The best man in the ship must take the helm.

16
00:02:25,072 --> 00:02:31,200
Then, with every mast head manned, the piled-up craft rolled down before the wing.

17
00:02:31,261 --> 00:02:42,416
The strange, upheaving, lifting tendency of the taff-rail breeze, filling the hollows of so many sails, made the buoyed, hovering deck to feel like air beneath the feet.

18
00:02:42,856 --> 00:02:51,248
While still she rushed along, as if two antagonistic influences were struggling in her one to mount direct to heaven.

19
00:02:51,228 --> 00:02:54,835
the other to drive yawingly to some horizontal goal.

20
00:02:55,135 --> 00:03:01,528
And had you watched Ahab's face that night, you would have thought that in him also two different things were warring.

21
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:09,784
While his one live leg made lively echoes along the deck, every stroke of his dead limbs sounded like a coffin tap.

22
00:03:10,846 --> 00:03:14,232
On life and death this old man walked.

23
00:03:14,212 --> 00:03:25,022
Well, but though the ship so swiftly sped, and though from every eye, like arrows, the eager glances shot, yet the silvery jet was no more seen that night.

24
00:03:25,862 --> 00:03:29,706
Every sailor swore he saw it once, but not a second time.

25
00:03:29,846 --> 00:03:35,771
This midnight spout had almost grown a forgotten thing, when, some days after, lo!

26
