but upon making sail to overtake it, once more it disappeared as if it had never been, and so it served us night after night, till no one heeded it but to wander at it, mysteriously jetted into the clear moonlight or starlight, as the case might be disappearing again for one whole day, or two days, or three.

29
00:04:03,402 --> 00:04:20,922
And, somehow seeming, at every distinct repetition, to be advancing still further and further in our van, this solitary jet seemed for ever alluring us on, nor with the immemorial superstition of their race, and in accordance with the preternaturalness, as it seemed,

30
00:04:20,902 --> 00:04:42,133
which in many things invested the Pequod, were there wanting some of the seamen who swore that whenever and wherever described, at however remote times, or in however far apart latitudes and longitudes, that unnearable spout was cast by one's selfsame whale, and that whale, Moby Dick.

31
00:04:42,113 --> 00:04:59,856
For a time there reigned, too, a sense of peculiar dread at this flitting apparition, as if it were treacherously beckoning us on and on, in order that the monster might turn round upon us, and rend us at last in the remotest and most savage seas.

32
00:04:59,996 --> 00:05:11,952
These temporary apprehensions, so vague but so awful, derived a wondrous potency from the contrasting serenity of the weather, in which, beneath all its blue blandness,

33
00:05:11,932 --> 00:05:29,805
Some thought there lurked a devilish charm, as for days and days we voyaged along, through seas so wearily, lonesomely mild, that all space, in repugnance to our vengeful errand, seemed vacating itself of life before our urn-like prowl, but—

34
00:05:29,785 --> 00:05:50,493
At last, when turning to the eastward, the Cape winds began howling around us, and we rose and fell upon the long troubled seas that are there, when the ivory-tusked Pequod sharply bowed to the blast and gored the dark waves in her madness, till, like showers of silver chips, the foam flakes flew over her bulwarks.

35
00:05:51,254 --> 00:05:58,324
Then all this desolate vacuity of life went away, but Dave placed his sights more dismal than before.

36
00:05:58,304 --> 00:06:04,192
Close to our bows, strange forms in the water darted hither and thither before us.

37
00:06:05,493 --> 00:06:26,100
While thick in our rear flew the inscrutable sea-ravens, and every morning perched on our stays, rows of these birds were seen in spite of our hootings, for a long time obstinately clung to the hemp, as though they deemed our ship some drifting uninhabited craft, our thing appointed to desolation.

38
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:29,687
And therefore a fit roosting-place for their homeless selves.

39
00:06:30,309 --> 00:06:44,899
And he did heave still and restingly heave the Black Sea, as if its vast tides were a conscience, and the great mundane soul were in anguish and remorse, for the long sin and suffering it had bred.

40
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:47,221
Cape of Good Hope, do they call ye?

41
00:06:47,442 --> 00:07:11,545
Rather Cape Tormentoto, as called of yore, for longer lured by the perfidious silences that before had attended us, we found ourselves launched into this tormented sea, where guilty beings transformed into those fowls and these fish, seemed condemned to swim on everlastingly without any haven in store, or beat that black air without any horizon.

42
00:07:11,525 --> 00:07:23,719
But calm, snow-white, and unvarying, still directing its fountain of feathers to the sky, still beckoning us on from before, the solitary jet would at times be described.

43
00:07:23,839 --> 00:07:33,550
During all this blackness of the elements, Ahab, though assuming for the time the almost continual command of the drenched and dangerous deck,

44
00:07:33,530 --> 00:07:39,739
manifested the gloomiest reserve, and, more seldom than ever, addressed his mates.

45
00:07:39,899 --> 00:07:49,713
In tempestuous times like these, after everything above and aloft has been secured, nothing more can be done but passively to await the issue of the gale.

46
00:07:50,774 --> 00:07:53,718
Then captain and crew become practical fatalists.

47
00:07:54,299 --> 00:08:01,309
So, with his ivory leg inserted into its accustomed hole, and with one hand firmly grasping a shroud,

48
00:08:01,289 --> 00:08:12,588
